This is the place that takes the cake. Best place in town to get an oil change while you wait in the car. Now some may think it's cheesy but i like how they take the time to explain the most minute detail of the process. These young men are courteous, respectful, and have the greatest attitude.  They offer you a drink and if you been here before they call you by your name. Plus! Plus you get a free car wash coupon good for thirty days at buggy car wash next door. < Text>
I was directed to park behind a car being serviced.  I expected a little wait time.  I waited, waited, another car parked behind me and we continued to wait for almost an hour. When I complained the young man said they had an older van in the middle bay and they did not have an oil filter that would fit.....really?  Why not move the van until the part arrived?? When my turn came I asked for the most expensive synthetic oil change and three wiper blades for my Tahoe. They only had 2 front windshield blades available which I purchased.  When all was done I gave the man my card to pay the $97.65.  He returned without a service receipt and told me they were "out of paper".  This is the large printout that explains what was done, what was checked etc. ( I believe it is required by state law).  Next he handed me a 3" x 5" piece of paper for an "exterior" only car wash.  I told him I always had free interior and exterior washes with a full service.  He responded by telling me their "policy has changed".  I have been a returning customer for a long time.  My next and future service needs will be at Red Carpet in Fresno.< /Text>

<time>1488927381044</time>< Review>
Went for an oil change. After I left two lights came on on my dash. Went right back they couldn't reset the lights so I took it to the dealership. There I was told my battery cables were messed with causing my truck's computer to reset. Toyota charged me $150 to reset the computer software. When I returned to Oulstop to give them the paperwork and notice from Toyota they refused to reimburse me. This happened at their location and instead they told me it wasn't their fault because it couldn't be "proved". The fact that I left the shop the lights came on and I turned around and went right back immediately to show them they still said it's not there problem. I won't be going back their. That oil change cost me $200 and all they would do is give me 50% off my next piece change... Yeah what a great compensation for messing my truck up! Terrible customer service as they wouldn't get back to me for over a week until I started calling them and requested the GMs number. He in turn refused to help as well. Never going back!< /Review>

< Text>
I don't even know where to begin. This place is a SCAM! They are really really good at selling the product but after your signe up, service and company is the absolute worst! I've been going thru this nightmare for about 2 years now and I advise everyone to stay away! Don't believe me, then check the better business bureau reviews. What they don't tell you is that in their policy its satisfaction guarantee and not money back guaranteed. Another thing is you never see or talk to the ortho. Another thing too, when Candid went live earlier in the day, I commented my opinions and got removed and blocked from the stream. I went ahead and looked them up with my secondary account, found them and commented again and again I got removed. Keep in mind I didn't say bad words just stated my opinion of DO NOT BUY and LOOK AT THE BETTER BUSINESS BUREAU REVIEWS  and again I got removed and blocked from live stream. Then I quickly created an account for my last attempt, found them and commented once more and again I was removed. There is so much I could say having 2 years dealing with this company. Your better off spending the extra money and goi with invisalign where you could at least see the ortho every so often, have the job done correctly and have the satisfaction and peace of mind knowing your teeth are 100% symmetrical. It's quality over quantity, always remember that. I know this is only 1 review of a few but you do you just don't regret it later. Ps if you decide to give them a chance make sure you log calls with time, agent and subject with notes so you can look back if needed as that's my mistake but honestly just stay away..Go check out the better business bureau and I wish you the best in your journey! It was so cool to see my teeth scanned onto the computer so I could see the areas I had problems with from multiple angles. Overall all of the team was very nice there and I‚Äôm grateful that they have a physical location where you can ask any questions and get scanned by a professional, instead of using a putty mold at home where you can make mistakes that prolong the process. I would definitely come here if you are looking for clear aligners at a decent price.</text>

<Text>Good customer service is becoming a lost art, but not at Candid!  As soon as I walked through the door of this pleasant clean, hip looking environment, I was warmly greeted by Alicia (pronounced ah-lee-CEE-ah), who was lovely and very welcoming.  After completing your information and medical history on a tablet, you're given a very nice bamboo toothbrush and toothpaste to prep for your intake exam.

Ashley was my technician -- she did the very high tech imaging and advised me about the aligner procedures and financing options.  She also was extremely welcoming and lovely, and just fun to hang with.  If I didn't have to use that spreader to hold my mouth open during the imaging process, we probably would have  laughed most of the time I was there!

I had traditional braces over 20 years ago and it took 2 years to straighten my teeth (and cost more than $3,000).  Unfortunately, I lost my retainer and over the years my teeth have shifted so that now my front gap has returned.  I am so excited to receive my Candid aligners and to have gorgeous, straight teeth in about 6 months -- for less than I paid for traditional braces!

Bottom line -- great atmosphere, great people, great experience, and straight teeth for far less money than going to an Invisalign dental office.  Yup, Yup!!!!!!< /Text><rating>5</rating><pictures>None< /pictures>< UserId.>

< Review>
BEST BIKE RENTALS @GOLDEN GATE PARK!

I don't normally write reviews but had an awesome experience with Avenue Cyclery this past weekend and wanted to share!

My dad and I were recently visiting SF and wanted to rent bicycles to explore the city a bit. We checked around at the different rental shops in that area and found the going rate to be ~$30/day.

After speaking with the super helpful staff, we rented two Trek FX2 bikes which came with a hex wrench and helmet included. The bikes were in great condition and were light and fast, perfect for riding in the city.

Shortly after renting and riding downtown, I had some maintenance issues. I immediately called Avenue Cyclery and they gave me directions to the closest bike shop I could walk to. I quickly got the bike repaired and continued riding.

When I returned, the awesome staff generously offered to work with me regarding the cost of maintenance and the rentals. They were super friendly, their main concern was that I had a good day riding in SF!

Long story short, if you're going to rent a bicycle by Golden Gate Park there is only one real choice! The staff was great and I will definitely be back next time I visit!</Review>

<user>100246053998295410004</user><time>1455054937871< /time><gmapID>0x808587516f485721:0x46f3d00a52ded989<//gmapID><response>None<//response><pictures>None< /pictures>< review>
Avenue Cyclery is pretty impressive. The customer service was awesome. I have always enjoyed riding bike as a little kid. I was here two weeks ago and asked for some city beginner riding advice.  Riding through Goldengate Park was a great experience. Going down Highway one at Ocean Avenue was quite the workout. From where we were at Goldengate was about a 5 mile bike ride.  According to Google it would take the average bike or 20 minutes to get to Goldengate. The person also mentioned a bike right towards Merced like would be a good idea for beginners. The bike selection was pretty rad. Although I didn't get an option of what color the bike was a gentleman helping us sized me up pretty good on the bike.  32 bucks for a bike rental that lasted three hours maybe a little more, for two people. Not a bad experience keep in mind I was told going down to the beach is downhill as you come up it's going to be an uphill battle.  Excited to get the ride started in a soon as it ended I was out of breath. Thank you Avenue Cyclery</review>

<text>I've never been in Boot Barn before. But, I've read a lot good reviews about Wrangler jeans and wanted to go somewhere other than Target and Walmart (they both carry Wrangler, but not deep selections).  Anyway, I looked at the BB website and found what I wanted, then called the nearest store.  A nice lady pulled the 2 exact models I wanted, in the correct size. < Review>
I am so very disappointed in Shepler's and Boot Barn.  If I could leave negative stars I would.  I have been a loyal customer for 20 years and have always enjoyed shopping in their retail stores.  Last month I placed my first online order, and today nearly three weeks later, my boots have still not arrived.  I alerted both Boot Barn and UPS the day my boots were to arrive, but did not, June 4th.  Today it's the 20th of June and I cannot get anyone at Boot Barn to help me.  They will not refund my money nor will they ship a new pair of boots.  They stated their 'policy' is to wait for UPS to conduct their internal investigation.  The problem is, nobody at Boot Barn is actively managing the situation with UPS, it's all on me.  I have never had a worse experience with an online retailer.  I do not nor should I care about Shepler's relationship with UPS.  The boots were lost or stolen, make a decision and provide some decent customer service.  At the very least, refund my money immediately.  I should not be expected to wait until 'UPS has finished their investigation'.  This is disappointing and upsetting, as I needed these boots when I ordered them, and paid for expedited shipping as well.  Multiple emails to Boot Barn, multiple emails and calls to UPS, and still no resolution.  Customer service works like this - keep your loyal customers happy and they stay with you.  If you do not, you lose them forever.  So sad that customer service does not exist at Boot Barn/Shepler's.  This is a far cry from the company of old.  A very loyal customer has now been lost forever.  Just refund my money and I will quietly move on to a retailer who is customer focused, and cares about my business.< /Review>

< review>
I have never been so disappointed and frustrated with a specific store that I felt the need to write a negative review but this Boot Barn in Lake Forest has the worst retail service I've ever seen. Management(an older man and a younger blonde woman) both times has been extremely irritable, condescending, unfriendly, and ultimately unhelpful. Once, I got to the store at 5:03 pm on a Sunday because I got off work a little early and rushed over to exchange a pair of unworn boots for an identical pair with a larger size, and the woman came over as I was coming in and told me she had already started closing and it was against her policy to let me in. Mind you they were not closed already, she basically kicked me out of the store because she wanted to leave at exactly 5 and was extremely unfriendly and rude about it. The other time I had an encounter with them was when I tried to exchange my brother's boots, unworn, for a larger size and was told that without a receipt or tags they wouldn't do it. He then proceeded to huff and puff about all the data he had to ask me about so he could look me up, like my telephone number... Ultimately I swapped them at different Boot Barn but will avoid this one at all costs and urge all others to do the same.</review>

< review>
I was waiting for my Grandma to get her hair done for over an hour and got to a point where I was so hungry I couldn't wait to eat. I stopped in to get a vegetarian torta which they don't have on the menu but she totally accommodated. The bread was toasted to the perfect crispiness the torta came with beans, cheese, lettuce, tomato, onion, and guacamole.
